In my electron app, I use following codes to create one simple test xlsx file and then use readFile to read it, but no any reponse. actually, any files in my electron app which cannot be read by  workook.xlsx.readFile, no any reponse and no any error throws.. 

Following codes to create test xlsx
async function test() {
    const workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
    workbook.creator = 'Me';
    workbook.lastModifiedBy = 'Her';
    workbook.created = new Date(1985, 8, 30);
    workbook.modified = new Date();
    workbook.lastPrinted = new Date(2016, 9, 27);
    const worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('My Sheet');
    worksheet.columns = [
      { header: 'Id', key: 'id', width: 10 },
      { header: 'Name', key: 'name', width: 32 },
      { header: 'D.O.B.', key: 'DOB', width: 10 }
    ];
    const data = [
        [1, 'electron','DOB'],
        [2, 'exceljs', 'DOB']
    ];
    worksheet.addRows(data);
    await workbook.xlsx.writeFile("c:\\\\temp\\\\test111.xlsx");
}

Following codes to use readFile() to test

